This paper deals with data structures for maintaining subsets of integers and performing operations on them efficiently. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also involves complexity theory (cs.CC) as it discusses the space and time complexity of the proposed data structures. The use of semipartitions and set coloring also suggests that the paper may be relevant to algebraic combinatorics (cs.AL) and graph theory (cs.GT).
